# Movie metadata



`app/generated/movie-metadata.js` is auto-generated. The file header states:



```text

// Auto-generated by scripts/generate-movie-metadata.ps1 - do not edit by hand.

// Re-run: npm run generate-metadata:ps

```



## Regenerating



1. Copy `.env.example` to `.env` and set `OMDB_API_KEY` (free key from omdbapi.com)

2. Run `npm run generate-metadata:ps` or `npm run bootstrap-metadata` for a full pipeline

3. Reload the browser to pick up the new file



## Listing keys



Metadata keys must match `movieDatabase` listing strings exactly in `app/main.js`.



`getMovieMetadata()` in `app/main.js` resolves listings and applies aliases (e.g. extended-cut variants).



## Poster overrides



Use `scripts/poster-overrides.json` when OMDb returns a bad or missing poster — do not patch individual entries in `movie-metadata.js`.



## When to regenerate



- After adding or removing movies from `movieDatabase`

- After changing a listing string (year, title spelling)

- Not needed for watched-list-only changes (`watched-movies.js`)
